NAME        anthocyanin 5-O-glucoside 6'''-O-malonyltransferase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Acyltransferases;
            Transferring groups other than aminoacyl groups
SYSNAME     malonyl-CoA:pelargonidin-3-O-(6-caffeoyl-beta-D-glucoside)-5-O-beta-D-glucoside 6'''-O-malonyltransferase
REACTION    malonyl-CoA + pelargonidin 3-O-(6-caffeoyl-beta-D-glucoside) 5-O-beta-D-glucoside = CoA + 4'''-demalonylsalvianin [RN:R06799]
ALL_REAC    R06799;
            (other) R07910
SUBSTRATE   malonyl-CoA [CPD:C00083];
            pelargonidin 3-O-(6-caffeoyl-beta-D-glucoside) 5-O-beta-D-glucoside [CPD:C12640]
PRODUCT     CoA [CPD:C00010];
            4'''-demalonylsalvianin [CPD:C12641]
COMMENT     Specific for the penultimate step in salvianin biosynthesis. The enzyme also catalyses the malonylation of shisonin to malonylshisonin [cyanidin 3-O-(6''-O-p-coumaryl-beta-D-glucoside)-5-(6'''-O-malonyl-beta-D-glucoside)]. The compounds 4'''-demalonylsalvianin, salvianin, pelargonidin 3,5-diglucoside and delphinidin 3,5-diglucoside cannot act as substrates.
